# Build-context exclusions for the crawler image (IMAGE-03 / CONFIG-02).
#
# Required exclusions (D-11): build artifacts + local/secret config must never
# enter the build context, so they can never be baked into the image.
target/
config.toml
config.*.toml
.env

# Additional exclusions (D-12): large, build-irrelevant trees kept out of the
# cargo-chef `COPY . .` context to keep transfers small.
.git/
.planning/

# NOTE (D-12, intentional): the `config.*.toml` glob above also matches the
# committed, non-secret `config.example.toml`. This is deliberate for Phase 6 —
# the build does not need `config.example.toml` in-context, so no narrower
# negation is added to re-include it.
#
# CRITICAL: do NOT add exclusions for the offline sqlx metadata dir or the
# migration sql dir. The builder stage compiles against the committed offline
# query metadata with SQLX_OFFLINE=true, and the sqlx migrate embed macro reads
# the migration sql directory at compile time. Excluding either breaks the build.
